(Common Failure Patterns) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Frequent causes of GPU miner issues:) Tj
T*
(- stale or mismatched OpenCL/CUDA drivers,) Tj
T*
(- running wrong platform binary,) Tj
T*
(- missing device permissions in containerized environments,) Tj
T*
(- overly aggressive batch sizes that trigger repeated timeout churn,) Tj
T*
(- strict mode enabled with no validated backend available.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(First-response sequence:) Tj
T*
(- run --probe,) Tj
T*
(- reduce batch size and timeout pressure,) Tj
T*
(- rerun strict audit,) Tj
T*
(- compare with CPU output for deterministic parity,) Tj
T*
(- verify binary hash metadata is current.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Security and Consensus Notes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The GPU miner does not alter consensus policy constants. Active production values remain:) Tj
T*
(- block target cadence 120s,) Tj
T*
(- retarget interval 180 blocks,) Tj
T*
(- fee floor 500 atoms/vB,) Tj
T*
(- tx confirmations 10, private tx confirmations 10, coinbase maturity 150.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(GPU acceleration changes throughput potential for hash search, not chain validity semantics.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
